<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD4AC76F44123E5FBE6F97C" bold="true" box="[1099,1122,1755,1775]" pageId="7">27</emphasis>
) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD4AC76F25523CCFDF2F895" bold="true" box="[607,630,1778,1798]" pageId="7">28</emphasis>
) sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD4AC76F32B23CCFCBCF895" bold="true" box="[801,824,1778,1798]" pageId="7">29</emphasis>
) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F308245BFCB6FEE9" blockId="8.[770,818,357,378]" box="[770,818,357,378]" pageId="8">1187</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F15E2491FDFFFD8B" blockId="8.[340,1248,430,536]" pageId="8">
Pronotum with weakly pronounced sexual dimorphism, weakly oblong () (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F47A2490FB38FE57" box="[1136,1212,430,452]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) to weakly transverse (). Elytra with moderate sexual dimorphism, 0.51 () to 0.57 () times as long as pronotum; puncturation fine, shallow, and relatively sparse; microsculpture very shallow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F15E2718FE75FD03" blockId="8.[340,1247,550,656]" pageId="8">
Abdomen rather shining; puncturation moderately sparse on tergite III-V, very sparse on tergites VI-VIII; microsculpture present, but very shallow; tergites 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFDBAC79F419277DFBCBFDCB" box="[1043,1103,579,600]" pageId="8">III-IV</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFDBAC79F48C277DFB2DFDCB" box="[1158,1193,579,600]" pageId="8">VII</collectionCode>
with sexual dimorphism; posterior margin of tergite 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFDBAC79F3372761FCE4FDE7" box="[829,864,607,628]" pageId="8">VII</collectionCode>
with indistinct narrow rudiment of a palisade fringe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F16327A1FDCEFC06" blockId="8.[340,1248,670,917]" pageId="8">
: pronotum weakly elongated posteriorly, posterior margin broadly and shallowly concave, occasionally truncate; elytra with relatively short and weakly elevated sutural carina extending along anterior half of suture; each elytron with extensive, but ill-defined and shallow impression; elytral puncturation weakly granulose (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F40027CCFBD8FC9B" box="[1034,1116,754,776]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFDBAC79F1A22631FE60FCB7" box="[424,484,783,804]" pageId="8">III-IV</collectionCode>
each with moderately pronounced median tubercle (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F4042630FBD8FCB7" box="[1038,1116,782,804]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFDBAC79F4B62631FB5BFCB7" box="[1212,1247,783,804]" pageId="8">VII</collectionCode>
with relatively short, stout (lateral view), slender (antero-dorsal view), erect, and apically rounded (antero-dorsal view) process (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F2F82678FCEEFCCF" box="[754,874,838,860]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Figs 24-25</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of sternite VIII indistinctly angled in middle (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F29D265DFD6DFCEA" box="[663,745,867,889]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); median lobe of aedeagus with dagger-shaped cristal process (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F1F82641FDBAFC06" box="[498,574,895,917]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F163269DFD77FC62" blockId="8.[340,1247,931,1009]" pageId="8">
: posterior margin of pronotum more or less truncate in the middle; elytra without impressions and with very fine sparse puncturation; sternite VIII broadly convex posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F18126E5FE52FC62" box="[395,470,987,1009]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
); spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F2AE26E5FD77FC62" box="[676,755,987,1009]" captionStart="Figs 20-29" captionStartId="7.[340,380,1710,1730]" captionTargetBox="[340,1248,785,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-147@7.[340,1253,1208,1685]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 20-29: Geostiba solodovnikovi sp.n. (20-23: holotype): (20) habitus; (21) head in lateral view; (22) pronotum and elytra; (23) anterior part of abdomen; (24) abdominal segment VII in lateral view; (25) tergite VII in antero-dorsal view; (26) sternite VIII; (27) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (28) sternite VIII; (29) spermatheca. Scale bars: 20: 1.0 mm; 21-26, 28: 0.2 mm; 27, 29: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434902/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Fig. 29.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F15E26C1FDCAFBA2" blockId="8.[340,1248,1023,1073]" pageId="8">
E t y m o l o g y: This species is dedicated to Alexey Solodovnikov, Chicago, who collected the 
<typeStatus id="3C5F2DA3FFDBAC79F1D12125FD83FBA3" box="[475,519,1051,1072]" pageId="8">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F15E2101FDCFFB57" blockId="8.[340,1248,1087,1221]" pageId="8">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: 
<taxonomicName id="24E4E882FFDBAC79F2A12101FC1FFBC6" authorityName="Homson" authorityYear="1974" box="[683,923,1087,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solodovnikovi">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFDBAC79F2A12101FC1FFBC6" box="[683,923,1087,1109]" italics="true" pageId="8">Geostiba solodovnikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily separated from most other Turkish representatives of 
<taxonomicName id="24E4E882FFDBAC79F2AA2165FCE7FBE2" box="[672,867,1115,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Tropogastrosipalia">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFDBAC79F2AA2165FCE7FBE2" box="[672,867,1115,1137]" italics="true" pageId="8">Tropogastrosipalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its small size, the pale coloration, and the small eyes. From all its consubgeners it is distinguished by the male primary and secondary sexual characters. For a supplementary key see the comparative notes in section on 
<taxonomicName id="24E4E882FFDBAC79F1A82191FD91FB56" authority="Homson, 1974" authorityName="Homson" authorityYear="1974" box="[418,533,1199,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biformis" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFDBAC79F1A82191FD91FB56" box="[418,533,1199,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8">G. biformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CAA3F268FFDBAC79F2112191FDCFFB57" box="[539,587,1199,1220]" pageId="8" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFDBAC79F15E21EDFC0FFAB3" blockId="8.[340,1247,1235,1313]" pageId="8">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d b i o n o m i c s: 
<taxonomicName id="24E4E882FFDBAC79F35E21EDFBC7FB7A" authorityName="Homson" authorityYear="1974" box="[852,1091,1235,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solodovnikovi">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFDBAC79F35E21EDFBC7FB7A" box="[852,1091,1235,1257]" italics="true" pageId="8">Geostiba solodovnikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from one locality in the Mescit Da÷ları (
<collectingRegion id="21205DE3FFDBAC79F30621D1FCECFA96" box="[780,872,1263,1285]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="8">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
) in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="9BF3D391FFDBAC79F42A21D1FBF3FA96" box="[1056,1143,1263,1285]" name="Turkey" pageId="8">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFDBAC79F48321D1FB57FA96" box="[1161,1235,1263,1285]" captionStart="Map 4" captionStartId="24.[340,385,1550,1570]" captionTargetBox="[340,1253,1038,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-17@24.[340,1253,1038,1526]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Map 4: Distributions of Geostiba solodovnikovi (square), G. elmaica (open circle), and G. priva (filled circle) in Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434930/files/figure.png" pageId="8">Map 4</figureCitation>
), where the 
<typeStatus id="3C5F2DA3FFDBAC79F1B42035FE70FAB3" box="[446,500,1291,1312]" pageId="8">types</typeStatus>
were collected at an altitude of 
<quantity id="241C3EE4FFDBAC79F33D2035FC02FAB3" box="[823,902,1291,1313]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="8" unit="m" value="2600.0">2600 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
